The paper discusses the development of ethical chatbots, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI. The paper also mentions the need for chatbots to engage in complex conversations with humans, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computational Linguistics). Additionally, the use of logic-based approaches implies that it could be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the ethical considerations of the chatbots could also place it in the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
